# Deny by default. Only inputs explicitly needed for the two wasm-pack builds
# and the runtime web trees can enter the build context.
**

!Dockerfile
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!src/
!src/**

!web/
!web/**
# Generated locally; the container rebuilds these from Rust sources.
web/pkg/
web/pkg-worklet/
# Browser/unit tests and package metadata are not runtime assets.
web/score/tests/
web/score/package.json

!training-prototype/
!training-prototype/*.html
!training-prototype/*.css
!training-prototype/*.js
!training-prototype/manifest.webmanifest
!training-prototype/js/
!training-prototype/js/**
!training-prototype/icons/
!training-prototype/icons/**
!training-prototype/vendor/
!training-prototype/vendor/**
# All 5 built-ins ship baked into the image, not just the tracked
# control_satb.musicxml: the other 4 are gitignored (not tracked in git) but
# are covered by the same owner-confirmed publication permission as the
# omr/out catalog (see training-prototype/omr/SOURCES.md, 2026-07-10) and are
# small/static reference pieces, not the actively-growing catalog. The shared
# tenant-site Helm chart supports exactly one PVC mount per container, already
# claimed by omr/out below -- baking these in avoids fighting that chart for
# a second mount for four files that rarely change. This ONLY works because
# .dockerignore filters the build context, not git tracking, so files that
# are gitignored but physically present on disk still enter the image unless
# explicitly excluded (which is exactly why the omr/ exclusions below are
# comprehensive, not selective).
!training-prototype/content/
!training-prototype/content/*.musicxml
!training-prototype/samples/
!training-prototype/samples/voices/
!training-prototype/samples/voices/**

# Defense in depth: no OMR code, source corpus, intermediates, verification
# output, or pipeline environment may enter the context. omr/out is the sole
# exception: the image creates it as an empty PVC mount point (populated at
# deploy time by scripts/publish_chanterlab_catalog.sh, infra repo) --
# everything else under omr/ is excluded below, unconditionally.
training-prototype/omr/
training-prototype/omr/**
training-prototype/omr/pdfs/
training-prototype/omr/pages/
training-prototype/omr/gt_crops/
training-prototype/omr/shots/
training-prototype/omr/verify/
training-prototype/omr/out/
training-prototype/omr/.venv/

# Never admit repository metadata, dependency trees, caches, local virtual
# environments, test fixtures, or build output even if a future allow rule is
# accidentally broadened.
.git/
.git/**
**/.git/
**/.git/**
**/node_modules/
**/node_modules/**
target/
target/**
**/target/
**/target/**
**/.venv/
**/.venv/**
**/venv/
**/venv/**
**/__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/**
**/tests/
**/tests/**
**/*fixture*/
**/*fixture*/**
